Rolls-Royce Bidding for $2.5 Billion Petrobras Deal, FT Reports

-- B y   G r a n t   S m i t h
-- 
2011-05-30T10:49:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/rolls-royce-bidding-for-2-5-billion-petrobras-deal-ft-reports.html
Rolls-Royce Group Plc (RR/)  is bidding on a
$2.5 billion contract to build turbine engines for  Petroleo
Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  as part of a plan to expand in  Latin America , the
Financial Times reported.  Rolls-Royce will compete with  General Electric Co. (GE)  for the
contract to construct 32 engines for offshore drilling
platforms, the newspaper said, Francisco Itzaina, chief
executive for Latin America.  The company intends to increase its employees in Latin
America to 700 in three years from 500 and plans to spend $120
million on projects, the FT said.  Rolls-Royce wants to at least double sales in the region by
2020 from about $700 million in 2010 as Brazilâ€™s oil sector
develops, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
